968
01:27:11,400 --> 01:27:13,500
I never got around to it, OK?

969
01:27:13,700 --> 01:27:16,800
I always thought
there was gonna be plenty of time!

970
01:27:17,000 --> 01:27:19,100
I'm sorry.

971
01:27:23,600 --> 01:27:25,900
I wish I didn't know about any of this.

972
01:27:27,400 --> 01:27:30,100
I wish I was like
everybody else in the world.

973
01:27:31,100 --> 01:27:33,200
Then tomorrow it would just be over.

974
01:27:36,300 --> 01:27:38,600
There wouldn't be any time to be sorry.

975
01:27:40,200 --> 01:27:42,100
About anything.

976
01:27:48,800 --> 01:27:50,700
Oh, Jesus!

977
01:27:51,900 --> 01:27:54,200
I really wanted to learn how to swim.

978
01:27:55,500 --> 01:27:57,400
I swear to God I did.

979
01:28:06,600 --> 01:28:08,800
Did I tell you that next week

980
01:28:09,900 --> 01:28:11,900
I was gonna be on TV?

981
01:28:12,000 --> 01:28:14,200
You're kidding?

982
01:28:14,600 --> 01:28:17,700
On that aerobics show
with some girls from my dad's class.

983
01:28:17,900 --> 01:28:19,800
A movie star.

984
01:28:20,000 --> 01:28:21,900
Yeah!

985
01:28:22,200 --> 01:28:26,500
It's kinda stupid, huh? I mean, nobody
would have been watching me anyway.

986
01:28:26,900 --> 01:28:28,000
I would have.

987
01:28:47,600 --> 01:28:49,000
Oh, Jesus!

988
01:28:49,200 --> 01:28:51,200
The bastard turned us in!

989
01:29:52,700 --> 01:29:54,600
It's all right. Get in.

990
01:30:21,200 --> 01:30:24,900
We have a launch detection.
We have a Soviet launch detection.

991
01:30:25,200 --> 01:30:27,100
BMEWS has confiirmed a massive attack.

992
01:30:27,400 --> 01:30:30,300
- Missile warning. No malfunction.
- Confiidence is high.

993
01:30:30,600 --> 01:30:33,600
- Cobra Dane, is this an exercise?
- This is not an exercise.

994
01:30:34,000 --> 01:30:37,500
General, DPS is tracking
300 inbound Soviet ICBMs.

995
01:30:44,300 --> 01:30:47,400
- Tell me this is one of your simulations.
- It's not, Jack.

996
01:30:47,700 --> 01:30:51,200
All right. Flush the bombers.
Get the subs in launch mode.

997
01:30:52,400 --> 01:30:54,400
We are at DEFCON 1 .

998
01:30:54,600 --> 01:30:55,600
DEFCON 1.

999
01:30:59,100 --> 01:31:02,700
Major Lem, get me a report on the WOPR.

1000
01:31:05,000 --> 01:31:08,400
Initial attack profile
is a full-scale Soviet strike.

1001
01:31:08,700 --> 01:31:12,500
WOPR is putting our losses
at 85 to 95% of the strategic forces.

1002
01:31:12,900 --> 01:31:15,200
What does WOPR recommend,
Mr McKittrick?

1003
01:31:15,400 --> 01:31:17,800
Full-scale retaliatory strike.

1004
01:31:19,400 --> 01:31:21,600
I need some machine to tell me that?

1005
01:31:21,800 --> 01:31:24,800
President's on his way
to join Airborne Command.

1006
01:31:25,200 --> 01:31:26,800
We have to give launch option.

1007
01:31:27,000 --> 01:31:30,500
- Has he spoken to the premier?
- The Russians deny everything.

1008
01:31:30,900 --> 01:31:33,200
We have a Soviet submarine
launch detection.

1009
01:31:34,000 --> 01:31:37,200
Let's go into a launch mode.
Close up the mountain.

1010
01:31:44,400 --> 01:31:47,600
This is Crystal Palace.
We're closing up the mountain.

1011
01:31:47,900 --> 01:31:50,900
After the gates are closed,
nobody gets in or out.

1012
01:31:57,800 --> 01:31:59,700
Initiate internal power.

1013
01:32:00,900 --> 01:32:02,900
Generators on and functioning.

1014
01:32:11,900 --> 01:32:13,900
External power disconnected.

1015
01:32:17,600 --> 01:32:19,500
Seal off ventilation shafts.

1016
01:32:19,700 --> 01:32:21,500
Shaft locks sealed.

1017
01:32:26,400 --> 01:32:28,400
The gate's closed!

1018
01:32:36,100 --> 01:32:37,900
Is everybody OK?

1019
01:32:38,100 --> 01:32:40,500
- Are you all right?
- Yeah. Run for it!

1020
01:32:44,100 --> 01:32:46,000
The gate's gonna shut! Come on!

1021
01:32:46,300 --> 01:32:48,200
Come on!

1022
01:33:00,600 --> 01:33:02,500
Hold the door! Hold the door!

1023
01:33:06,400 --> 01:33:08,600
Hold the goddamn door!

1024
01:33:13,600 --> 01:33:15,500
Come on! Hurry!

1025
01:33:18,300 --> 01:33:20,200
They're clear! They're clear!

1026
01:33:39,200 --> 01:33:43,000
All units confirm weapons targeted
and ready. Awaiting launch codes.

1027
01:33:43,300 --> 01:33:45,200
We are in a launch mode.

1028
01:33:45,500 --> 01:33:47,700
Major Lem, lock out changes.

1029
01:33:47,900 --> 01:33:49,900
Roger. Lock out enabled.

1030
01:34:00,000 --> 01:34:01,900
All right. I'll call you back.

1031
01:34:02,100 --> 01:34:04,500
Here!

1032
01:34:11,300 --> 01:34:14,400
I don't know what you think
you can do here, Stephen.

1033
01:34:14,600 --> 01:34:18,200
John! Good to see you!
I see the wife still picks your ties.

1034
01:34:18,500 --> 01:34:21,700
- What has this kid been telling you?
- How far has it gone?

1035
01:34:21,900 --> 01:34:27,100
The president's ready for a counterstrike.
That's what we're recommending he do.

1036
01:34:29,100 --> 01:34:32,600
- It's a bluff, John. Call it off.
- No, it's not a bluff. It's real.

1037
01:34:32,900 --> 01:34:35,500
Hello, General Beringer? Stephen Falken.

1038
01:34:36,300 --> 01:34:39,200
Mr Falken, you picked
a hell of a day for a visit.

1039
01:34:39,400 --> 01:34:43,500
General, what you see
on these screens up here is a fantasy.

1040
01:34:43,900 --> 01:34:46,600
A computer-enhanced hallucination.

1041
01:34:46,900 --> 01:34:50,000
Those blips are not real missiles.
They're phantoms.

1042
01:34:50,300 --> 01:34:54,300
There's nothing to indicate a simulation.
Everything's working perfectly.

1043
01:34:54,600 --> 01:34:57,200
- Does it make any sense?
- Does what make any sense?

1044
01:34:57,600 --> 01:34:58,400
That!

1045
01:34:58,600 --> 01:35:02,000
Look, I don't have time
for a conversation right now.

1046
01:35:02,200 --> 01:35:05,500
General, are you prepared
to destroy the enemy?

1047
01:35:05,900 --> 01:35:06,800
You betcha!

1048
01:35:06,900 --> 01:35:10,800
- Do you think they know that?
- I believe we've made that clear enough.

1049
01:35:11,100 --> 01:35:12,900
Then... don't.

1050
01:35:13,100 --> 01:35:16,000
Tell the president to ride out the attack.

1051
01:35:16,300 --> 01:35:18,400
Sir, they need a decision.

1052
01:35:19,400 --> 01:35:22,800
General, do you really believe
that the enemy would attack

1053
01:35:23,100 --> 01:35:26,300
without provocation,
using so many missiles and subs,

1054
01:35:26,500 --> 01:35:29,800
so that we would have no choice
but to totally annihilate them?

1055
01:35:30,100 --> 01:35:32,400
One minute and 30 seconds to impact.

1056
01:35:32,600 --> 01:35:35,200
General, you are listening to a machine.

1057
01:35:36,300 --> 01:35:38,600
Do the world a favour
and don't act like one.

1058
01:35:43,600 --> 01:35:46,000
One minute and 20 seconds to impact.

1059
01:35:58,000 --> 01:35:59,300
Yes, Mr President.

1060
01:35:59,500 --> 01:36:03,500
Sir, at this point in time, we cannot
positively confirm the inbounds.

1061
01:36:03,900 --> 01:36:06,500
We have reason to believe
they may not exist.

1062
01:36:06,800 --> 01:36:09,000
Yes, sir. That's affirmative.

1063
01:36:10,600 --> 01:36:11,600
Yes, sir.

1064
01:36:11,900 --> 01:36:13,100
I do, too.

1065
01:36:13,300 --> 01:36:15,300
One minute to impact.

1066
01:36:16,200 --> 01:36:18,100
Who's first and how soon?

1067
01:36:18,400 --> 01:36:21,200
Initial impact
in the 43rd Bomb Wing at Loring,

1068
01:36:21,500 --> 01:36:24,500
319th at Grand Forks,
and Alaskan Air Command, Elmendorf.

1069
01:36:24,700 --> 01:36:26,600
50 seconds to impact.

1070
01:36:26,900 --> 01:36:29,800
Get me the senior controllers.
I wanna talk to 'em myself.

1071
01:36:30,100 --> 01:36:32,100
All stations, this is Crystal Palace.

1072
01:36:32,300 --> 01:36:35,000
Stand by for a message from Brass Hat.
Acknowledge.

1073
01:36:35,400 --> 01:36:38,900
ElmendorfAirForce Base Operations.
Lieutenant Colonel Bowers.

1074
01:36:39,100 --> 01:36:42,100
319th Bomb Wing Operations.
Colonel Chase.

1075
01:36:42,400 --> 01:36:47,400
Colonel, this is Loring AirForce Base.
The senior controllerisn't here right now.

1076
01:36:47,800 --> 01:36:49,800
That's all right. Who are you?

1077
01:36:50,000 --> 01:36:52,600
Sir, this is Airman Dougherty, sir.

1078
01:36:53,900 --> 01:36:56,000
This is General Beringer at NORAD.

1079
01:36:56,300 --> 01:36:58,200
Our current situation...

1080
01:36:59,400 --> 01:37:02,400
Men, we're currently tracking

1081
01:37:02,800 --> 01:37:05,800
approximately 2,400 inbound
Soviet warheads.

1082
01:37:06,000 --> 01:37:08,500
But at the moment
we cannot confirm this.

1083
01:37:08,700 --> 01:37:11,200
I repeat, we cannot confirm this.

1084
01:37:11,500 --> 01:37:13,300
30 seconds to impact.

1085
01:37:14,000 --> 01:37:18,000
We're right there with you guys.
We've taken all the steps we can.

1086
01:37:19,000 --> 01:37:21,500
Stand by to launch missiles
at my command.

1087
01:37:29,300 --> 01:37:31,600
Stay on this channel as long as you can.

1088
01:37:31,900 --> 01:37:33,800
We'll be standing by.

1089
01:37:34,000 --> 01:37:36,000
20 seconds to impact.

1090
01:37:46,000 --> 01:37:48,300
Ten... nine...

1091
01:37:48,700 --> 01:37:51,400
eight... seven...

1092
01:37:51,700 --> 01:37:53,000
six...

1093
01:37:53,100 --> 01:37:54,800
five...

1094
01:37:55,000 --> 01:37:56,000
four...

1095
01:37:56,300 --> 01:37:57,500
three...

1096
01:37:57,700 --> 01:37:58,800
two...

1097
01:37:59,100 --> 01:38:01,100
one... Impact.

1098
01:38:18,400 --> 01:38:20,500
This is Crystal Palace. Are you still on?

1099
01:38:22,600 --> 01:38:26,800
This is Crystal Palace.
Are you still on? Anyone there?

1100
01:38:27,800 --> 01:38:29,700
That's affiirmative, sir.

1101
01:38:31,100 --> 01:38:32,300
Yeah! We're here!

1102
01:38:32,600 --> 01:38:36,000
- Jesus H Christ! We're still here!
- Our boards are showing impact.

1103
01:38:37,800 --> 01:38:41,200
No, sir. No impact. We're alive and well.

1104
01:38:41,400 --> 01:38:42,800
All right!

1105
01:38:43,400 --> 01:38:44,800
All right!

1106
01:38:50,100 --> 01:38:52,100
All right!

1107
01:38:58,600 --> 01:39:00,800
All right! Recall the bombers!

1108
01:39:01,100 --> 01:39:03,100
Stand down the missiles!

1109
01:39:34,800 --> 01:39:37,200
Joshua, what are you doing?

1110
01:39:40,500 --> 01:39:42,800
COC, I need Dr McKittrick right away.

1111
01:39:43,700 --> 01:39:46,100
- This is McKittrick.
- Sir, we got a problem.

1112
01:39:46,300 --> 01:39:48,400
WOPR's not letting me log back on.

1113
01:39:48,700 --> 01:39:51,900
- I can't get in to stand down the missiles.
- Stand by.

1114
01:40:04,900 --> 01:40:06,400
Paul, this is McKittrick.

1115
01:40:06,600 --> 01:40:08,800
The WOPR's not letting us back in.

1116
01:40:09,000 --> 01:40:12,400
I know. No one can get back on.
We're trying everything.

1117
01:40:12,700 --> 01:40:16,000
It's like the entire password file
has been wiped out.

1118
01:40:16,300 --> 01:40:19,000
I tried that! Don't you think
I would have tried that?

1119
01:40:22,500 --> 01:40:24,300
What are those?

1120
01:40:24,400 --> 01:40:26,400
Those are launch codes.

1121
01:40:26,600 --> 01:40:28,500
What are they for?

1122
01:40:28,800 --> 01:40:32,800
Joshua's trying to find the right codes
so he can launch the missiles himself.

1123
01:40:43,500 --> 01:40:44,500
What's happening?

1124
01:40:44,800 --> 01:40:47,100
The random number generators
aren't running.

1125
01:40:47,400 --> 01:40:49,300
- Got anything?
- I'm still looking.

1126
01:40:49,600 --> 01:40:52,100
I got no idea.
It could be coming from anywhere.

1127
01:40:54,200 --> 01:40:56,300
Sir, you better get on the headset.

1128
01:40:58,400 --> 01:40:59,400
Yeah?

1129
01:40:59,600 --> 01:41:04,500
General, the machine has locked us out.
It's sending random numbers to the silos.

1130
01:41:04,800 --> 01:41:06,700
Codes. To launch the missiles.

1131
01:41:07,000 --> 01:41:08,900
Just unplug the goddamn thing!

1132
01:41:09,200 --> 01:41:12,300
- Jesus Christ!
- That won't work, General.

1133
01:41:12,500 --> 01:41:15,700
It would interpret a shutdown
as the destruction of NORAD.

1134
01:41:15,900 --> 01:41:20,500
The computers in the silos would carry
out their last instructions. They'd launch.

1135
01:41:20,900 --> 01:41:24,100
- Can't we disarm the missiles?
- Over a thousand of them?

1136
01:41:24,500 --> 01:41:28,300
There's no time. At this rate
it'll hit the launch codes in 5.3 minutes.

1137
01:41:30,600 --> 01:41:34,200
Mr McKittrick?
After very careful consideration, sir,

1138
01:41:34,600 --> 01:41:38,700
I have come to the conclusion
that your new defence system sucks.

1139
01:41:39,800 --> 01:41:42,600
I don't have to take that,
you pig-eyed sack of shit.

1140
01:41:42,900 --> 01:41:47,600
I was hoping for something a little better
than that from a man of your education.

1141
01:41:48,000 --> 01:41:49,900
General, it's the president.

1142
01:41:54,900 --> 01:41:57,700
What do you...
What are you gonna tell him?

1143
01:41:59,100 --> 01:42:02,100
That I'm ordering our bombers
back to fail-safe.

1144
01:42:02,300 --> 01:42:05,300
We might have to go through
this thing after all.

1145
01:42:08,200 --> 01:42:09,100
Yes, sir.

1146
01:42:16,300 --> 01:42:19,600
He's got one. When he gets all ten,
he'll launch the missiles.

1147
01:42:20,000 --> 01:42:23,200
- Well, can't they get in and stop it?
- No. They can't.

1148
01:42:25,900 --> 01:42:28,700
They've taken out my password.

1149
01:42:29,000 --> 01:42:31,700
- Well, what are we gonna do?
- I don't know. Do you?

1150
01:42:32,100 --> 01:42:35,300
I told you not to start
playing games with that thing.

1151
01:42:39,400 --> 01:42:40,600
It's games.

1152
01:42:42,600 --> 01:42:44,700
- Games!
- Try it.

1153
01:42:44,900 --> 01:42:48,400
- John, feed it a tapeworm.
- Too risky. It might smash the system.

1154
01:42:48,600 --> 01:42:51,200
- Did the kid get in the back door?
- We took it out.

1155
01:42:51,500 --> 01:42:53,800
- Invade the deep logic.
- We hit a fire wall.

1156
01:42:54,000 --> 01:42:57,000
If it wants to play a game, then play it.
Have it list games.

1157
01:42:57,200 --> 01:43:00,000
- For Christ's sake!
- He's played before.

1158
01:43:00,300 --> 01:43:02,500
- He can hardly do worse.
- Two numbers.

1159
01:43:02,800 --> 01:43:05,500
I'd piss on a spark plug
if I thought it'd do any good.

1160
01:43:05,700 --> 01:43:08,300
- Let the boy in there, Major.
- List games.

1161
01:43:14,500 --> 01:43:16,000
Chess.

1162
01:43:23,400 --> 01:43:24,900
Three numbers locked in.

1163
01:43:25,100 --> 01:43:26,300
Poker.

1164
01:43:29,100 --> 01:43:32,400
Security system's
not gonna let anything through.

1165
01:43:35,000 --> 01:43:36,900
Global thermonuclear war.

1166
01:43:45,800 --> 01:43:47,200
Four numbers.

1167
01:43:49,700 --> 01:43:52,000
Stephen, for Christ's sake. Do something.

1168
01:43:52,200 --> 01:43:54,500
- Come on, kid. Let's go.
- No. Try again.

1169
01:43:57,700 --> 01:43:59,900
- Put the list back up.
- We already tried that.

1170
01:44:00,200 --> 01:44:01,900
- Put it up!
- Yes, put it up.

1171
01:44:10,000 --> 01:44:12,700
- It's not on the list!
- What's not on the list?

1172
01:44:13,000 --> 01:44:14,800
Go ahead. It's got to be somewhere.

1173
01:44:17,800 --> 01:44:20,900
Tic-tac-toe.

1174
01:44:27,100 --> 01:44:29,800
You're in. Order it to disarm the missiles.

1175
01:44:30,000 --> 01:44:31,100
No! No.

1176
01:44:41,000 --> 01:44:43,200
Five numbers. It's got half the code.

1177
01:44:45,000 --> 01:44:46,600
One.

1178
01:44:48,200 --> 01:44:50,100
- Put X in the centre square.
- I know.

1179
01:45:01,400 --> 01:45:03,600
- Six up.
- There's no way you can win.

1180
01:45:03,800 --> 01:45:06,700
I know that. It doesn't. It hasn't learned.

1181
01:45:07,000 --> 01:45:11,400
- Is there any way to make it play itself?
- Yes. Number of players zero.

1182
01:45:32,500 --> 01:45:33,800
Seven!

1183
01:45:34,100 --> 01:45:36,500
Come on. Learn, goddamn it.

1184
01:45:49,500 --> 01:45:50,600
Eight.

1185
01:45:50,800 --> 01:45:55,100
It must be caught in a loop. It's taking
power from the rest of the system.

1186
01:45:56,300 --> 01:45:58,100
Nine numbers.

1187
01:46:02,200 --> 01:46:05,100
Ten! It's got the code. It's going to launch.

1188
01:46:23,600 --> 01:46:26,300
Colonel Conley, call SAC.
Get me a launch status report.

1189
01:46:29,100 --> 01:46:31,000
Major Davis, get me the president.

1190
01:47:04,100 --> 01:47:05,500
How you doin', Colonel?

1191
01:47:05,700 --> 01:47:09,100
Land lines out of the mountain are dead.
I'm trying satellites.

1192
01:47:34,500 --> 01:47:37,200
- What's it doing?
- It's learning.

1193
01:48:24,800 --> 01:48:27,400
Greetings, ProfessorFalken.

1194
01:48:36,500 --> 01:48:39,000
Hello, Joshua.

1195
01:48:39,900 --> 01:48:41,700
Strange game.

1196
01:48:41,900 --> 01:48:45,100
The only winning move is not to play.

1197
01:48:53,300 --> 01:48:56,400
How about a nice game ofchess?

1198
01:49:33,100 --> 01:49:36,600
Colonel Conley, take us to DEFCON 5.

1199
01:49:36,900 --> 01:49:38,900
Yes, sir.

1200
01:52:40,400 --> 01:52:42,600
Visiontext subtitles: Sally Lewis

